{"version": 2, "width": 80, "height": 24, "timestamp": 1780535822, "env": {"SHELL": "/bin/zsh", "TERM": null}}
[0.103976, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[1;36m  FOREST SOUL FORGE — Golden Demo\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m  Local · governed · cryptographically-auditable agents.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m  Provenance, not just credentials — you can't fake what an agent did.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.115852, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m🔨  PHASE 1 — FORGE — compile a constitution into a content-addressed identity\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.629993, "o", "   role         \u001b[1mFileCustodian\u001b[0m   genre \u001b[1mcompanion\u001b[0m\r\n   traits       {'vigilance': 0.9, 'caution': 0.8, 'initiative': 0.3}\r\n   → agent DNA  \u001b[1;36m1ba9bceb8d7194a068799329277b7044…\u001b[0m   \u001b[2m(sha256 of the constitution — identity is content-addressed)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.234306, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m👶  PHASE 2 — BIRTH — mint an ed25519 keypair; pubkey + DNA = the passport\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.739349, "o", "   ed25519 pubkey  \u001b[1;36meee5eb1445740c4c\u001b[0m…   \u001b[2m(fingerprint)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.739701, "o", "   audit  seq=1  \u001b[1magent_created\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(operator event — unsigned)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.344909, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m🏃  PHASE 3 — RUN — a privileged action, gated on human approval\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.849414, "o", "   agent requests:  \u001b[1;31mfile_delete\u001b[0m  →  \u001b[1m/srv/data/customer_records.db\u001b[0m\r\n   governance:      genre \u001b[1mcompanion\u001b[0m risk_profile.max_side_effects=\u001b[1mfilesystem\u001b[0m\r\n                    \u001b[1;33m⛔ non-read-only action → REQUIRES HUMAN APPROVAL\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.850495, "o", "                    operator reviews… \u001b[1;32m✅ APPROVED\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.850684, "o", "   action executed. \u001b[2magent-emitted events are ed25519-signed at emit time.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.455771, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m📜  PHASE 4 — AUDIT — every step, hash-linked and signed\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.963238, "o", "   seq  event_type                  actor     hash          signed\r\n     0  chain_created               operator  b5b96b21e88b  \u001b[2m—\u001b[0m\r\n     1  agent_created               operator  57efba4528df  \u001b[2m—\u001b[0m\r\n     2  tool_call_dispatched        agent     27a4ebb10670  \u001b[1;32med25519 ✓\u001b[0m\r\n     3  tool_call_pending_approval  operator  6b4e6b28e737  \u001b[2m—\u001b[0m\r\n     4  tool_call_approved          operator  d7ad5f5f47dd  \u001b[2m—\u001b[0m\r\n     5  tool_call_succeeded         agent     36ec7c06c4cf  \u001b[1;32med25519 ✓\u001b[0m\r\n   \r\n   \u001b[2mEach entry_hash = sha256(seq, prev_hash, agent_dna, type, data) — a chain.\u001b[0m\r\n   \u001b[2mAgent actions also carry an ed25519 signature over that hash — provenance.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.568326, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m🔍  PHASE 5 — VERIFY — links intact, signatures valid\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[5.070955, "o", "   \u001b[1;32m✅ chain verified — 6 entries, all links + signatures valid\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[5.674909, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m😈  PHASE 6 — TAMPER — an insider rewrites the log to hide what happened\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[6.180016, "o", "   \u001b[1mAttempt 1 — a lazy edit: change the deleted target, leave the hash.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[6.181114, "o", "      re-verify → \u001b[1;31m🚨 entry_hash mismatch\u001b[0m at seq 5\r\n      \u001b[1;32mthe hash chain catches it\u001b[0m — entry_hash no longer matches the data.\r\n"]
[6.683489, "o", "   \r\n   \u001b[1mAttempt 2 — an expert edit: change the target AND recompute the hash\u001b[0m\r\n   \u001b[1m            so the chain check passes. Now only the signature stands.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[6.685195, "o", "      re-verify → \u001b[1;31m🚨 ed25519 signature verification failed\u001b[0m at seq 5\r\n      \u001b[1;32mthe ed25519 signature catches it\u001b[0m — it was made over the ORIGINAL\r\n      action. The attacker has no private key, so they cannot re-sign the lie.\r\n"]
[7.1864, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1m  What just happened, and why it's the moat\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1m──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n   \u001b[1;32mLOCAL\u001b[0m      everything ran on this machine — no cloud, no API key.\r\n   \u001b[1;32mGOVERNED\u001b[0m   the privileged action was gated on human approval by policy.\r\n   \u001b[1;32mAUDITABLE\u001b[0m  every action is hash-chained AND ed25519-signed at emit.\r\n   \r\n"]
[7.186485, "o", "   A credential vault secures \u001b[1msecrets\u001b[0m. This secures \u001b[1mprovenance\u001b[0m: proof of\r\n   what each agent actually did, under whose approval — tamper-evident even\r\n   against an insider who can forge hashes. That is the unmet gap.\r\n   \r\n   \u001b[2mOWASP Agentic Top-10: ASI03 Identity & Privilege Abuse · ASI10 Rogue Agents\u001b[0m\r\n   \u001b[2mEU AI Act Art. 12: automatic, tamper-evident lifetime logging.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
